# Production (VPS / live server). Copy to .env.production before: pnpm build
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Do NOT copy .env.local to the server — .env.local overrides .env.production and
#   would keep localhost URLs and break the live site.
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are inlined at build time; change them → rebuild (pnpm build).
#
# Browser API base (inlined at build).
#
# RECOMMENDED (especially for https://bcf.so): leave NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL **unset**.
# The browser calls same-origin `https://bcf.so/api/...`; Next.js proxies to Go (no CORS, no mixed content).
#
# NEVER set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL to a Docker service name (e.g. http://go_backend:8080) — browsers cannot
# resolve it and it breaks HTTPS sites (mixed content if you use http://).
#
# Optional: public https:// API URL only if Go is exposed on its own HTTPS origin (same-site or CORS configured).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# Server-only: where the Next.js container reaches the Go API (Docker network). Required for /api proxy.
# API_INTERNAL_URL=http://go_backend:8080

# Same value as backend DASHBOARD_WRITE_KEY (server-only, not exposed to browser).
DASHBOARD_WRITE_KEY=change-me-long-random-string

# Backend Go (same machine or Docker): set PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://yourdomain.so and optionally
# CERTIFICATE_QR_SITE_URL (see backend/.env.example) so certificate PDF QR codes open /verify on phones.
